    comment: "Matched filter without downsampling\nor decimation to be able to see\
      \ eye diagram.\nIn both, the Tx and Rx filter, the number of \ntabs is set to\
      \ a multiple of sps such that\nthe total delay introduced by the filters\nis\
      \ also an integer multiple of sps, i.e.\nof the discrete-time symbol period."
    decim: '1'
    gain: np.sqrt(sps)
    interp: '1'
